TY  - JOUR
T1  - Delegation and Leader-Member Exchange: Main Effects, Moderators, and Measurement Issues
AU  - Schriesheim, Chester A.
AU  - Neider, Linda L.
AU  - Scandura, Terri A.
Y1  - 1998/06/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256909
DO  - 10.5465/256909
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 298
EP  - 318
VL  - 41
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Subordinate and supervisor leader-member exchange (LMX) were examined as correlates of delegation and as moderators of relationships between delegation and subordinate performance and satisfaction. Raw score analyses of data on 106 dyads showed both to be significantly related to delegation and to have similar main and moderating effects for subordinate performance and satisfaction. Finally, within- and between-groups analyses largely supported the level-of-analysis predictions of the LMX approach. Implications for future LMX research are discussed.
AB  - Subordinate and supervisor leader-member exchange (LMX) were examined as correlates of delegation and as moderators of relationships between delegation and subordinate performance and satisfaction. Raw score analyses of data on 106 dyads showed both to be significantly related to delegation and to have similar main and moderating effects for subordinate performance and satisfaction. Finally, within- and between-groups analyses largely supported the level-of-analysis predictions of the LMX approach. Implications for future LMX research are discussed.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256909
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256909
Y2  - 2026/04/24
